---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import ProfilePhoto from '../assets/Hero-Image.JPG';
---

<section id="about" class="bg-brutal-black py-20 px-6" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  <div class="container mx-auto max-w-6xl">
    <!-- Section counter -->
    <div class="text-brutal-grey text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-4 reveal">/01</div>
    <h2 id="about-heading" class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brutal-white uppercase tracking-tight mb-16 reveal" data-delay="1">
      About
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12">
      <!-- Profile photo -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-4 reveal" data-delay="2">
        <div class="border border-brutal-rule aspect-[3/4] relative overflow-hidden bg-brutal-black">
          <Image
            src={ProfilePhoto}
            alt="Kamil Rogozinski standing in a city square"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            width={576}
            height={768}
            sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 30vw, 80vw"
            loading="lazy"
            format="webp"
          />
          <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-1 bg-brutal-red"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bio -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-8 reveal" data-delay="3">
        <p class="text-brutal-white/80 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          I build things for the web and I like hard problems. Most of my time is spent deep in a terminal&mdash;writing code, breaking things on purpose, and wiring up systems that actually work. Vim is my editor. The CLI is my home. If there's a harder way to do something that teaches me more, I'll probably take it.
        </p>

        <p class="text-brutal-white/80 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Lately I've been sharpening my technical writing and design eye. Good code deserves clear explanation, and a well-designed interface does half the communication for you. I care about the craft on both sides of the screen.
        </p>

        <p class="text-brutal-white/80 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          If you're working on something interesting and need someone who can ship clean code and think through the details&mdash;let's talk.
        </p>

        <!-- Tech stack grid -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-8">
          <div class="brutal-card !p-4 text-center">
            <div class="text-brutal-red text-2xl font-bold mb-1">FE</div>
            <div class="text-brutal-grey text-xs uppercase tracking-widest">React / Astro</div>
          </div>
          <div class="brutal-card !p-4 text-center">
            <div class="text-brutal-red text-2xl font-bold mb-1">BE</div>
            <div class="text-brutal-grey text-xs uppercase tracking-widest">Node / Spring</div>
          </div>
          <div class="brutal-card !p-4 text-center">
            <div class="text-brutal-red text-2xl font-bold mb-1">TS</div>
            <div class="text-brutal-grey text-xs uppercase tracking-widest">TypeScript</div>
          </div>
          <div class="brutal-card !p-4 text-center">
            <div class="text-brutal-red text-2xl font-bold mb-1">DB</div>
            <div class="text-brutal-grey text-xs uppercase tracking-widest">SQL / NoSQL</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Social links (text-based) -->
        <nav aria-label="Social media links" class="flex flex-wrap gap-6 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest">
          <a href="https://github.com/Kameleon21" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-brutal-grey hover:text-brutal-red transition-colors">GitHub</a>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kamil-rogozinski/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-brutal-grey hover:text-brutal-red transition-colors">LinkedIn</a>
          <a href="https://x.com/KamilRogozinski" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-brutal-grey hover:text-brutal-red transition-colors">X</a>
          <a href="mailto:kamilrogozinski29@gmail.com"
            class="text-brutal-grey hover:text-brutal-red transition-colors">Email</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
